&lt;div style="color: #5f6368; overflow-x: auto; overflow-y: hidden; width: 100%;"&gt;&lt;table border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9641%;"&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="width: 98.1839%;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;If the Protected Users security group cannot be used, at a minimum, privileged accounts should be protected against delegation by configuring the account with the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-style: italic; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Account is Sensitive and Cannot Be Delegated&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="vertical-align: baseline;"&gt; flag in Active Directory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
